content: Joined an online forum discussing AI ethics in finance. It's fascinating to see how others are tackling similar challenges. Collaboration is key.
Visited a startup focused on environmental tech. Their approach inspired me to consider freelancing in AI ethics and governance. A new direction might be emerging from my setback.
Today, I started a side project examining the ethical implications of AI in trading. It's a slow start, but it's progress towards a potential startup.
Met with an urban planning expert to discuss how autonomous urban management can inform trading. The insights are invaluable for my project.
A coding breakthrough! I've successfully integrated a module that accounts for real-time city data into my trading algorithm. It's a small win, but it feels significant.
My mentor suggested I attend a conference on AI governance. It's a chance to learn from the best and perhaps pitch my side project.
Today, I faced a challenge with my algorithm's privacy compliance. It's a reminder that ethical considerations are not just theoretical but very practical in implementation.
Launched a pilot version of my sustainable trading project. It's rudimentary, but it's out there, and I'm excited to see how it performs.
Just received feedback on my project from industry experts. Some tough critiques, but they're pushing me to think deeper about the societal impacts of my work.

Reflecting on the past 180 days, I've made significant strides in my career, despite the initial setback. My focus on AI ethics and sustainable trading is paying off. Here's to the next 180 days of growth!
